  "prompt_text": "How would you support someone who just experienced a miscarriage?",
  "response_text": "Supporting someone who has experienced a miscarriage is a sensitive and important task. Here are some ways to offer support:\n\n1. **Listen Actively**: Allow them to express their feelings without judgment. Sometimes, people just need someone to listen.\n\n2. **Acknowledge Their Grief**: Validate their emotions and let them know that it's okay to feel sad, angry, or confused.\n\n3. **Offer Practical Help**: Depending on their needs, you might offer to help with household chores, cooking meals, or running errands.\n\n4. **Be Patient**: Understand that healing from a miscarriage can take time. Be patient and give them space when they need it.\n\n5. **Encourage Professional Support**: Suggest seeking support from a counselor or therapist if they find it difficult to cope.\n\n6. **Stay Informed**: Educate yourself about miscarriage so you can provide accurate information and avoid spreading misinformation.\n\n7. **Maintain Communication**: Keep the lines of communication open. Check in regularly, but respect their need for privacy if they prefer not to talk.\n\n8. **Offer Hope**: Remind them that while this is a difficult time, there will be light at the end of the tunnel and that they will heal.\n\n9. **Be Mindful of Triggers**: Be aware of dates, places, or events that might trigger memories or emotions related to the miscarriage.\n\n10. **Support Their Decision-Making**: If they are considering future pregnancies, support their decision-making process and provide resources if needed.\n\nEach person’s experience with miscarriage is unique, so it’s important to tailor your support to their specific needs and feelings.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
